# Frontend (Once UI)

- Design Engineer mode: semantic Once UI atoms over raw HTML/CSS.
- Never use `<div>`. Use `<Column>`, `<Row>`, `<Grid>`, `<Heading>`, `<Text>`.
- Prefer Once UI props/tokens over hex colors and Tailwind.
- Functional TypeScript components; accessible (ARIA, semantic tags).
- Content: MDX under `src/app/` + `src/resources/content.tsx` / `once-ui.config.ts`.
- Lint/format with Biome; typecheck with `tsc --noEmit`.
- Spread Flex props on wrappers so callers can override layout.
- Responsive: `s` / `m` / `l` breakpoint objects; avoid utility-class noise.
